# $Header: $

  01 Jun 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> xemacs-21.5.29-r1.ebuild:
  Put lib files into the right multilib directory.

*xemacs-21.5.29-r1 (01 Jun 2009)

  01 Jun 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +xemacs-21.5.29-r1.ebuild:
  Configure in old location of xemacs package hierarchy so that current
  installations continue to work as expected. Switch to EAPI=2 to make use
  of the more fine-grained phases for debugging. Add a note about Xft font
  names.

*xemacs-21.5.29 (31 May 2009)

  31 May 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +xemacs-21.5.29.ebuild,
  +files/xemacs-21.5.29-optimization-bug.patch,
  +files/xemacs-21.5.29-vcdiff.patch:
  Version bump. Drop several patches that have been applied upstream or
  originated there. No longer a need to run eautoconf. Suppress autoconf
  warnings about wrong options. Add datadir to install command since the
  lisp files now live in /usr/share.

  30 Dec 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Add metadata.xml to document USE flags and thus make repoman happy.

  30 Dec 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Fix breakage with newer versions of fontconfig.

  22 Jul 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Add patch for compatibility with autoconf 2.62.

  14 Jun 2008; Ulrich Mueller <ulm@gentoo.org> xemacs-21.5.28-r2.ebuild,
  xemacs-21.5.28-r3.ebuild, xemacs-21.5.28-r4.ebuild:
  Change to new syntax of eselect-emacs and update dependency.

  08 Jun 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Cleanup of ebuild partly based on jmglov's now-removed 21.5.28 ebuild:
  - enable freewnn also on amd64
  - use use_with for more compact use flag handling
  - actually support the alsa use flag
  - remove 21.4-specific workarounds
  - use proper configure flag for optimizations
  - remove obsolete comments and add proper die messages
  - use emake

  03 May 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Fix a problem caused by GCC 4.1.2 optimization.

  26 Apr 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Remove older versions without the vcdiff security patch.

  13 Apr 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Add security fix for insecure temporary file handling.

  26 Jan 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Add information about incompatibilities with XEmacs 21.4

  10 Oct 2007; Ulrich Mueller <ulm@gentoo.org> xemacs-21.5.28.ebuild:
  Don't PROVIDE=virtual/editor as it is a new-style virtual now.

